LIMPOPO – Each learner is unique. One learner might retain information and study in a way that is not very effective for their classmate, or they might excel in a different area in school than their friends. While some learners might achieve wonderful things in arts and creative writing, their best friend or fellow classmate might find mathematics, science and technical subjects more fun to participate in. Taking the initiative to understand what learners would like to see more of in their school can help teachers and parents to understand learners’ interests and guide schools to provide top-quality learning opportunities. It will also provide a safe platform for learners to experiment in new skills and hobbies in an academical environment they are exposed to and feel safe in. Review asked learners what they would like their school to have in 2023 that it did not have in 2022: 